</div><br>
<span style="font-family: Poppins;">{{Class Variable|class=Deadzone|banner-text=white|color-h=331.91|color-s=87.3%|color-l=50.59%|hexagon=[[File:HeartWithHaloSymbol.png|link=|250px|center]]|safety=Insurmountable Cognitive Hazards|security=Strictly Uninhabitable|entity=Sustained Entity Population}}</span>
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">'''Level 888''', nicknamed as '''"Inocentia"''' or '''"Frostfall"''', is the 889<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms. It is a massive, frigid terrain consisting of a barren forest surrounded by hillsides. This level houses several unique [[Entity List|entities]] that collectively form an ecological system which, while self-sufficient, is particularly effective at entrapping humans via manipulation of the psyche. There is no known way to mitigate any of the effects instigated by these [[Entity List|entities]].</span>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''DESCRIPTION'''</center></big></big></big></span>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Image|file=Level 888 (I have really asked for permission, look at the credits in the bottom of the page).jpg|caption=<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Photo taken during mild weather.</span>|bgcolor=blank|bordercolor=red|fontsize=15px}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
The most explored and understood area of '''Level 888''' is its wooded landscape. It is entirely comprised of deciduous trees and shrubbery which are either dead or dying. Temperatures here have been measured as low as -34°C (-29.2°F) and as high as -5°C (23°F). The day/night cycle is evenly divided within a 40 hour period, and seasonal changes are negligible to non-existent. Though it resembles snow, the white powder covering the ground is a form of diatomaceous earth with concentrations of crystalline silica considered toxic to humans. In fine enough consistencies, this dust can form a cloud that hangs in the air when disturbed. Visibility is limited by an ever-present fog made up of said powder as well as sulfuric acid, water, and trace amounts of unknown compounds. It is recommended to wear protective clothing and utilize the best respiratory apparatus available while inside this level.

Exploration teams that crossed the edge of the forest have deduced that the area has a diameter of roughly 1400 km (~850 mi). Beyond that lies a series of rolling hills and plains, the overall size of which remains undetermined. Larger deposits of faux snow and harsh winds make traversal here especially perilous. Wanderers who ventured into this region have either perished from exposure or exited the level before finding any alterations in topography or notable landmarks. For reasons unknown, none of the human remains discovered at '''Level 888''' have displayed signs of the [[Phenomenon 35#Stages of the Wretched Cycle|Wretched Cycle]] in any stage.

Any well-known [[Entity List|entities]] (excluding the exclusive ones found within the premises) have been observed to not intake the same effects with humans, with their deaths being more peculiar and less researched. Within the first few hours, the entity shall start going mentally insane, with common signs being slashed trees and shrubbery.<ref><span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Many instances of these have happened, usually accompanying the cadavers of [[Entity List|entities]].</span></ref> Subsequently, the entity is met with death within two to three hours after they enter, but if the entity does not succumb, changes will happen within their body, ranging from lacerations to dismantling body parts. It is rare for any entity to survive after this part, but no regular entity has survived for more than 21 hours.
</span>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''ENTITIES'''</center></big></big></big></span>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Show Siphonaps Info'''</big></span></div>|body=
{{Image|file=SiphonapHD.jpg|caption=<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Malnourished juvenile Siphonap.</span>|bgcolor=blank|bordercolor=red|fontsize=15px}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Siphonaps''', also known as ''Saliens pulicis'', are translucent insects that are similar in anatomy to fleas, typically growing up to 20 cm (7.8 in) in length with a maximum leaping distance of approximately 12 m (~40 ft). The barbs on their legs act as hooks to assist in keeping a firm grip on a wide variety of surfaces. They are known to submerge themselves in areas with a thick coat of faux snow and lie in wait before bursting out and directly latching onto their prey. Their bites inflict little pain due to a numbing agent secreted from their mouths.

The initial bite of a '''Siphonap''' draws a small amount of blood in proportion to its body size, as its main purpose is to carry the numbing agent into the bloodstream. Once enough is introduced, it causes a rapid onset of changes to the victim's mental state. Symptoms include an overwhelming sense of hopelessness, derealization, deterioration of self-worth, and a desire to seek the nearest source of "comfort," namely other [[Entity List|entities]]. These effects will wear off after two hours unless another dose is administered. '''Siphonaps''' prefer to gather near sources of heat and will avoid causing immediately lethal damage to exothermic lifeforms.
</span>
|final=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Hide Siphonaps Info'''</big></span></div>}}
{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Show Broodweavers Info'''</big></span></div>|body=
{{Image|file=Broodweaver.jpg|caption=<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">A sketch of a Broodweaver made by a wanderer.</span>|bgcolor=blank|bordercolor=red|fontsize=15px}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Broodweavers''', also known as ''Homo pallidus'', are bloated, pale humanoids reaching 4.3 m (14 ft) in height, with a bundle of tendrils hanging from their face that conceals any other features. Due to their vestigial legs, they are unable to stand fully erect and possess limited mobility. '''Broodweavers''' have formed a symbiotic relationship with Siphonaps wherein they allow them to burrow shallow holes into their backs to create nests. In turn, the Siphonaps will occasionally venture out to find prey and lead it towards their hive after it has been reduced to a vulnerable state.

Once something is within suitable range, the '''Broodweaver''' will grab it and firmly cup it against its chest to ensure that it cannot escape. It then drapes its tendrils over the captive and latches onto its head with its main set of mandibles. This initiates a slow process in which a significant portion of the individual’s memory is assimilated. Memories, particularly ones from an organism's youth, provide sustenance for the '''Broodweaver'''. Based on circumstantial evidence, it is believed that those involving stress and trauma are especially nutritious.

To aid in keeping its source of food alive for as long as possible, the '''Broodweaver''' will insert a specialized tube into the victim's throat or navel that pumps out a purple-colored slurry once every 20 hours.<ref><span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">In the case of the navel, the tube will pierce the intestinal wall with minimal damage inflicted.</span></ref> The only somewhat safe time to be near a '''Broodweaver''' is during its feeding on another person, as it will promptly discard anything with a lower level of sapience in favor of commanding its hive to attack a human.
</span>
|final=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Hide Broodweavers Info'''</big></span></div>}}
{{Collapse|num=3|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Show Shroudstalkers Info'''</big></span></div>|body=
{{Image|file=Shroudstalker.jpg|caption=<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Attempted photo of a fleeing Shroudstalker.</span>|bgcolor=blank|bordercolor=red|fontsize=15px}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Shroudstalkers''', also known as ''Caligo hiders'', are leech-like creatures with multiple sets of arms running down their sides and a vertical bisection along the entirety of their heads. Eyewitness accounts report them as being around 3 m (9.8 ft) in length. Photographing them has proven difficult due to anomalous streaks of light obfuscating their form, which are thought to be a self-defense mechanism that activates when threatened. These lights also persist post-mortem for an indeterminate amount of time.

While they are estimated to have a ground speed of 10 m/s (22 mi/h), '''Shroudstalkers''' are averse to direct engagement. They instead act as scavengers, opting to steal from roaming Siphonaps or wait until a Broodweaver discards its prey, as it will usually still be alive. Though these are their favored methods, they have also been inclined to ambush sleeping humans on multiple occasions. In any case, they will quickly constrict their quarry with immense force by using their appendages as anchor points before dragging it to an isolated location and initiating a series of shrill vocalizations. These serve both to deter other predators and soothe the victim, despite the fact that they are not rooted in any existing language.

Once its captive becomes calm, the '''Shroudstalker''' will inflict a severe injury upon it, usually by snapping a bone or causing blunt force trauma with its tail. This cycle of inducing pain and the subsequent nurturing of its prey back to a relative state of good health and peaceful demeanor is how the '''Shroudstalker''' feeds. It is particularly obsessed with obscuring the damage it causes from the naked eye, almost always ensuring that bones break cleanly and that bruises are hidden from view. It will simply toss its meal aside once its pain response becomes overly dulled.
</span>
|final=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Hide Shroudstalkers Info'''</big></span></div>}}
{{Collapse|num=4|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Show Amicas Info'''</big></span></div>|body=
{{Image|file=Amica.png|caption=<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Drawing uploaded by an unknown wanderer.</span>|bgcolor=blank|bordercolor=red|fontsize=15px}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Amicas''', also known as ''Glabes canini'', are stocky, bipedal mammals with numerous deformities. They superficially resemble hairless canines, except they do not possess anything below the ribcage nor a lower jaw. Aside from humans, these serve as the main source of food for other [[Entity List|entities]] that dwell in the forest. They subsist on the byproducts and carcasses of others using an egregiously inefficient digestive system that absorbs nutrients through a small bladder before the remainder is regurgitated. Between this and a myriad of other health defects, their natural life cycle rarely extends beyond 10 to 20 days.

When an '''Amica''' comes into contact with a comparatively large lifeform, it will develop an immediate and inseparable attachment to it. The rest of its life will be spent in service of its bonded partner, be it human or entity. This sense of loyalty is completely unwavering, with documented cases of '''Amicas''' remaining unresistant to intentional harm up to and including the point of expiration. If any other being approaches its partner in an aggressive manner, it will attempt, however ineffectually, to defend it. Some have noted that they will engage in "play" behavior when prompted.

Upon an '''Amica'''<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><nowiki>'</nowiki></span>s inevitable demise, whether by outside factors or natural causes, its chosen companion will enter a state of grief that lasts for several weeks. This only amounts to slightly dulled movements for [[Entity List|entities]]. On the other hand, humans will often experience near-catatonic depression and refuse basic necessities for days at a time. In extreme cases, this will lead to loss of life via dehydration or starvation. Those who have bonded to an '''Amica''' are at risk of suffering these effects even if they have already exited '''Level 888'''. It is fairly easy to avoid them, as they move too sluggishly to catch up to any person jogging at a moderate pace.
</span>
|final=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Hide Amicas Info'''</big></span></div>}}
{{Collapse|num=5|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Show Outer Being(s) Info'''</big></span></div>|body=
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
The only entity that has been observed in the lands outside of the forest. Very few wanderers have come into contact with it, and all accounts of its appearance vary wildly. Reported inconsistencies in physical attributes are as follows:

*Its number of respective limbs, torsos, eyes, mouths, etc., ranges anywhere from none to several hundred thousand.
*Its size has been described as "a bit smaller than a skyscraper," "a great, wide mountain," "stretching into the sky infinitely," "the same as me," and "he doesn't have a size because he's actually inside of your eye."
*Its skin is "scaly," "like water but darker than nothingness," "as smooth as silken sheets," "pretty normal I suppose," and "as if all of Noah's ark was made as one."
*Its movements are "blindingly fierce," "more gentle than my mother's," "on a plane that isn't for me to see," "in step with my own," and "unquestionably euphoric."

The only prevailing similarity is that no witnesses have ever described it using a pejorative. In fact, they refuse to speak negatively of it in even the slightest regard. Any human who either attempts to converse with this entity or looks directly at it for an extended period undergoes a permanent change in their psychology, adapting the following personality characteristics:

*A heightened sense of empathy.
*Above-average sociability and an outgoing demeanor.
*Willingness to trust those they meet, including strangers.
*The compulsion to hug anyone that they see.<ref><span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">None of the traits listed include discrimination between humans and [[Entity List|entities]].</span></ref>
</span>
|final=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Hide Outer Being(s) Info'''</big></span></div>}}
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''COMMUNITIES AND SETTLEMENTS'''</center></big></big></big></span>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
Due to the level's settings and conditions, any Community or Settlement is impossible to establish.
</span>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''ENTRANCES AND EXITS'''</center></big></big></big></span>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''ENTRANCES'''</center></big></big></big></span>
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
*There is a small chance of noclipping into '''Level 888''' while experiencing emotional distress within many nature-based levels and/or areas across the Backrooms.<ref><span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">No-clipping can affect individuals as well as groups, even if only one person within the group meets the criteria.</span></ref> Some notable instances are from [[Level 10]], [[Level 35]], [[Level 45]], [[Level 150]], or [[Level 300]].
*A second way to get into '''Level 888''' is by burning the doll from the hut in [[Level 110]], and escape into the woods. This causes great feelings of anguish and distress, ending up being transported into '''Level 888'''.
*A third way one might have a chance to get into '''Level 888''' is by getting transported by [[Level 154]]'s [[Level 154#The_Neon_Express|Neon Express]]'s rare One of a Kind miscellaneous trains, having a chance of bringing one into '''Level 888'''.
*A fourth way one might get into '''Level 888''' is by no-clipping during the [[Level 191#Winter Wonderland|Winter Wonderland]] phenomena in [[Level 191]], having a chance of leading into '''Level 888'''.
*A fifth way to get into '''Level 888''' is by pressing the button 9 repeatedly on the elevator in [[Level 366]]. This causes the elevator to malfunction, knocking one out, and waking up in '''Level 888'''.
*The current, final way one might get into '''Level 888''' is by reaching the termination point of the Dreadxit in [[User:Terraria is good... for reasons./Rip699pointsix|Level 455]], having a chance of leading into '''Level 888'''.
</span>
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''EXITS'''</center></big></big></big></span>
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
*Defeating and subsequently terminating a '''Broodweaver''' or '''Shroudstalker''' that has targeted one as prey can cause to be transported into [[Level 63]]. While it is not guaranteed, the odds are significantly bolstered by consuming its flesh within five hours of its passing.
*Interacting with an '''Outer Being''' will eventually result in being warped elsewhere. This exceedingly rare occurrence has so far resulted in being transported whether to [[Level 11]], [[User:SetaCraft/Sandbox:Level 394 (Archive)|Level 394]], or [[Level 974]].
*Certain areas might be warmer than usual during the day, or colder than usual during the night. Exploring these areas for long enough can lead one into the [[User:SetaCraft/Sandbox:Level 888.1 (Archive)#The Mainland|Mainland]] of [[User:SetaCraft/Sandbox:Level 888.1 (Archive)|Level 888.1]] eventually.
*'''''You succumbed to the cold, falling asleep in a snowbank. You woke up on an [[Level 889|ocean shore]]...'''''
</span>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Poppins;"><big><big><big><center>'''LOGS'''</center></big></big></big></span>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Collapse|num=6|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Open Interview Log 888-1'''</big></span></div>|body=
<div style="background: black; color: white; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 9px; border:solid white">
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Interviewer:''' Dr. Simon Evansfield
<br>
'''Interviewee:''' Ava Alis
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
'''<Begin Log>'''

'''Evansfield:''' Before anything, I'd like to thank you for agreeing to this interview.

'''Alis:''' No thanks needed. And it's a pleasure to meet you. I'm Ava.

'''Evansfield:''' ''[Chuckle.]'' My name is Simon. You're very well-mannered, but I suppose you get that a lot.

'''Alis:''' It depends. I get it more now than I used to. But it honestly doesn't feel like I’ve changed that much...since I met him.

'''Evansfield:''' You're referring to the '''Outer Being''', correct?

'''Alis:''' That's what you call him?

'''Evansfield:''' My theory is that it's a pending title until we can pull together something concrete. Between you and me, the name will stick at this rate.

'''Alis:''' ''[Giggle.]''

'''Evansfield:''' I hope you realize that it's not often someone returns from where you have, let alone in the manner that you did. Anything we can glean from you could be of great benefit to future generations.

'''Alis:''' That's why I'm here. At least, I like to think so.

'''Evansfield:''' Excellent. Now, can you remember anything about the entity? Anything distinctive?

'''Alis:''' Just that he was creating.

'''Evansfield:''' What now?

'''Alis:''' When we ran into him, he was in the middle of creating, like, everything! He tore away his own body, and he kneaded it into the big, fat guys. Then he ripped off their legs and molded the doggies from the leftovers. His veins became snakes. Or maybe those were his arteries? I'm not very good with anatomy...um, his blood turned into all those little creepy-crawlies. And after everything was over, he scattered his bones to the wind. Like you do with ashes.

'''Evansfield:''' That...

''[Silence.]''

'''Evansfield:''' Why do you think it did all that?

'''Alis:''' Funnily enough, I actually asked him why. He told me that someday it might change, but that this was how it had to be. And he...he didn't seem happy about it. I got the feeling I shouldn't press any more after that.

'''Evansfield:''' Did anything else happen?

'''Alis:''' Not really. I didn't have time to stand around. Lynn was in bad shape. I asked him if we could leave, and he said he'd take us to an exit. Then we ended up here.

'''Evansfield:''' I see. I know this might be hard, Ava, but since then...your state of mind...

'''Alis:''' Do you need a hug, Simon?

'''Evansfield:''' Do I- Ava, I don't think that would exactly be-

'''Alis:''' ''[Chair scraping.]''

'''Both:''' ''[Rustling.]''

'''Evansfield:''' ''[Clearing throat.]'' Thank you, Ava.

'''Alis:''' No problem!

'''Evansfield:''' You know, I had a daughter just like you, once.

'''Alis:''' I had a feeling you did.

'''Evansfield:''' Well, I...I suppose that will be all, for now.

'''<End Log>'''
