{{Collapse|num=7|initial=<div style="text-align: center;><span style="color:red; font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;"><big>'''Open Interview Log 888-2'''</big></span></div>|body=
<div style="background: black; color: white; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 9px; border:solid white">
<span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">
'''Interviewer:''' Dr. Simon Evansfield
<br>
'''Interviewee:''' Lynn Odagrau
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
'''<Begin Log>'''

'''Evansfield:''' Please, have a seat. I'm grateful for your cooperation with us.

'''Odagrau:''' Don't thank me. I didn't want to come. Ava convinced me otherwise.

'''Evansfield:''' I'll have to give her my regards, then. Your name?

'''Odagrau:''' Lynn. Don't you already know that?

'''Evansfield:''' And your relationship with Ava would be...?

'''Odagrau:''' Excuse me? Isn't this about what happened?

'''Evansfield:''' Yes, well, this is just for the record. A formality. I'm sorry if I offended you.

'''Odagrau:''' ''[Sigh.]'' She's like a little sister to me. It's been that way ever since we met.

'''Evansfield:''' In the Backrooms, presumably?

'''Odagrau:''' What do you think?

'''Evansfield:''' Mm...so you were traveling together, prior to-

'''Odagrau:''' Yeah. We- yeah. I can't exactly place why, but I feel like it was my fault that we ended up inside that Hell. We were lucky to have face masks on us. I gave Ava most of our equipment. Shielded her when those fucking bugs came after us, too. I remember her calling out to me for a while, and then...it's hard to describe.

'''Evansfield:''' There's no rush.

'''Odagrau:''' It was like I was taken back home. I saw my mom, as clear as day. I smelled her cooking. Felt her hands. Heard the wind chimes on the back porch. And every now and then, it got muddled. There was this blank space of just...haziness. It didn't dawn on me until I had time to think about it. But now I know for sure.

'''Evansfield:''' And that is?

'''Odagrau:''' I don't remember my father.

'''Evansfield:''' I'm...sorry to hear that.

'''Odagrau:''' Yeah. That's how anyone would respond. It took something important from me, after all. And yet I don't know how to feel. It's like I'm stuck in some kind of limbo. I try to look on the bright side, that I was rescued before it could steal anything else.

'''Evansfield:''' That was a Quick Match squad, correct? Team "Liam"? We already have their report.

'''Odagrau:''' Must have been. There was more on my mind than their rank and file. All they did was piss that monster off, so we made a run for it until we met up with the rest of the team. They already had Ava, thank God. We were fixed up and given breathing devices. My lungs were burning at that point, but at least they didn't get any worse. We stuck with them until we woke up one day and they had just...vanished.

'''Evansfield:''' Our communications don't paint a good picture. They're filed as KIA.

'''Odagrau:''' Damn. Figures. After that, we tried to press forward and lay low. There was no fucking way we could have taken on anything in that place. I guess by sheer dumb luck we found the edge of the forest. We both decided there was no turning back.

'''Evansfield:''' How far did you make it into the plainlands?

'''Odagrau:''' I don't know. Not very, I think. I was weak and delirious at that point. The bandages around my stomach kept seeping. I remember that was the only warmth I could feel. And then...Ava stopped. And I knew he was in front of us.

'''Evansfield:''' Just to verify, you didn't keep your eyes on it?

'''Odagrau:''' I couldn't. He was...he was too much for me. That's it.

'''Evansfield:''' So Ava is the only one afflicted, then.

'''Odagrau:''' Don't call it that. Never call it that.

'''Evansfield:''' Apologies, that's not what I...it must be terribly dangerous, is all. She's a bright girl, but any entity poses far more of a threat if you don't recognize it as a threat in the first place.

'''Odagrau:''' No.

'''Evansfield:''' Pardon?

'''Odagrau:''' You're wrong. It's a little harder, sure, but she knows not to go running towards them. And we're at [[Level 11]] now, anyway. You don't really have to worry about entities here. No, in the end, it's not them. It's...God...

'''Evansfield:''' Lynn?

'''Odagrau:''' It's people. People are the danger.

''[Silence.]''

'''Odagrau:''' I'm...I'm such a failure. I couldn't even...

'''Evansfield:''' It's alright. I'm stopping the tape. We're done here.<ref><span style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Poppins;">Shortly after conducting these interviews and filing the appropriate paperwork, Dr. Evansfield took a temporary leave of absence from his position, citing fatigue as the main reason.</span></ref>

'''<End Log>'''
</span>
